records.addlTxt:
Defendant in custody appearing via zoom from Dodge Correctional Institution.   
State moves to delete the penalty enhancers on counts 3 and 5.   Motion granted.   
Count 3 - Keeper of drug house - No contest plea.   
Count 5 - Possess cocaine with intent to deliver - No contest plea.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in counts 1, 2, 4, & 6.   Motion granted.    
Counts 3 and 5 - Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total sentence of five (5) years, two (2) years initial confinement, followed by three (3) years on extended supervision, on each count, concurrent and concurrent with 14 CF 481.   Conditions of extended supervision are: 
1) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process; 
2) Maintain absolute sobriety except for prescriptions taken in prescribed doses; 
3) Submit to random urine screens and pay for same; 
4) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination; 
5) Submit DNA sample; 
6) AODA assessment and follow through; 
7) Pay costs of action; 
8) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Court finds the defendant is eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program.   
Defendant has credit for 164 days already served.    
Minutes.
